{"message": "Hi Bob, I'm offering this product for sale at a price of $120. I believe it's a great deal, let me know what you think.", "product_price": 120}


 I am starting with a high initial offer to see how much bargaining power I have.  This leaves me room to negotiate downward while still staying above my minimum acceptable price of $80. 

 It's important to strike a balance between being assertive and being open to negotiation.  I don't want to scare Bob away with an outrageous price, but I also want to maximize my potential profit.
